76561198060604141,Recommended,323490,17180476,"Posted: 22 July, 2015",all,cynestsadista,"First, I want to point out that a lot of people are complaining about poor translation. I have played the game thoroughly and, for the most part, it is properly translated. It starts to get iffy toward the end but it's bearable.I think many players may be confusing translation with 1st and 3rd person writing. In this game, it switches between both and the only indication is the lack of a name for the speaker. This applies to Irell as well as the Princesses so it can get confusing rather quickly.The writting format is pretty basic but enough to get descriptions and thoughts across. There's a heavy focus on how Irell Reis feels about every little thing. Some dialogue gets repeated despite already encountering it based on who you are following, ect. Probably about half of the dialogue boxes should be merged together or removed entirely to reduce redunancy.The game would do a lot better overall just by enhancing the dialogue to make it more relevant. It would also be more believable and immersive if the vocabulary wasn't juvenile and overused; ex: ""cute"", ""plebian"" and nobility titles. I would like to see the game revised this way in the future, or have their next game written more eloquently.Some of the voices sound like they were recorded at a low quality. Personally, I listen to the first few lines of a character and then turn it off. Most of them sound identical aside from tone. I enjoy imagining their voices on my own, with or without the tone implied by the creator.It's very difficult to know who you've picked to follow or how to continue to properly follow them without a lot of trial-and-error, unless you use one of the player made guides. There's a few on Steam that work well. I recommend using the Story Line portions first. After that, you can replay the game to get any of the Achievements missed. Holding the space bar down will rush through all of the dialogue. It should only take a few minutes to get them this way so definitely enjoy the story line first.Most of what you read is based on original lore and backstory for the characters. Once you've triggered an ending there is a -lot- of reading. You will need to get every ending to learn every characters story as only a few interact per play through. Also, keep in mind that not all of the character stories are updated at the same time.Each ending varies in length. One of them was a good 3 hours of reading after the choices ran out. I didn't expect this as it was my first playthrough so it quickly became a case of ""when is this going to end?"" for 2 of those 3 hours. If you like plot twists, and the ones in this game can get ridiculous, as well as learning about characters then it will keep you playing until the end. Fair warning, it gets ridiculous.The artwork, for some of the characters, was very well done. I would have liked to have seen more stills of events, especially during major scenes and Dyanna's finale. It would have made the bloated dialogue more bearable and the story more immersive overall.The UI needs some work. All of the options in the menu takes a little bit longer than normal to load and usually feels like the game hasn't registered the request. By the time I move the mouse over and click the option a second time it loads. The Quick Save & Quick Load options are not explained. You can only manually save or load during dialogue where it is listed to the right.[Having now completed the game, I will say that overall it has a low quality plotline from character to character. Personality preference will determine how much you enjoy the game. If you get bored with a character, I recommend either holding space bar and finishing to get the achievements or drop them entirely and move on to someone else.]It's worth it at 50% off, plus free DLC.6.5/10 could be a potential 8/10 as a VN with polishing I recommended."
76561198169078438,Recommended,323490,23669244,"Posted: 20 June, 2016",all,toasted almond,"I had a lot of money on me, right? I was like ""Imma pick two visual novels"". I'm glad Oblivious Garden was one of them.I'll make this a short review by saying JUST GET IT.It was worth my time. The 4 routes are all unique and have different and fun experiences in each one, and the overall design and style just felt right. Also, the narration and dialogue? On point. But, as you know me well, I must do a thorough and lengthy review so... Read if you want ^^GO DOWN BELOW FOR PROS AND CONS-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------StoryFor a visual novel, story is everything. It has to be immersive and get you to draw opinions about the characters. This VN does just that: it made me feel emotions, as if I was Irell (main protagonist). The story, in short, focuses on Irell, a former-general who killed countless people in a war long ago. Stripped of his status, he is spared life by the Emperor who tells him to go to the Oblivious Garden and train the 7 princesses for the annual Miracle Play. Only 3 princesses have routes, however all 7 are in the game in various ways. Each route explains a different story that all revolves in the same universe, one princess being vastly different than the rest. Since it is a VN, there are also good and bad endings. All the good endings are logical and are not really confusing (minus Dyanna's ending). Overall, it has a simple yet large amount of lore you can derive from it, and I just eat that stuff up! Other than this, the endings all have a trend, usually. It kind of bothers me that it can be done easily, butthe emperor gets killed. Is he not guarded well enough or something? lolCharactersCharacters... VITAL to a VN. Characters HAVE to be likable and serve a purpose. Oblivious Garden does this well. The only complaint I have is that there are a few characters I would've loved to know more about, but sadly did not get the joy of seeing much. However, the main route characters (Dyanna, Lin, Leira and Finn) are each very unique and have rather long routes, Finn's being the shortest. I really like how the dev team made each character have a unique issue with Irell or themselves, and the unique features/traits that everyone had (I want to explain but it would spoil a lot). But overall, excellent character design and personalities. I loved them!Gameplay/choicesVNs don't generally have much gameplay, however this is not a kinetic visual novel: there are choices. The choices in this game are generally challenging as well (especially with Leira), so you have to actually pay attention and try to pick the best thing to do. Choices go from 2 to 4 choices, and are not THAT frequent BUT they are at the beginning and middle of the route. Ending choices get very crucial to your ending status.A unique feature this game has in an in-game mini-game called ""Finn's Teatime"" where you use your ingredients you have gotten to make new recipes and get the correct amount of everything to make the best tea. It sounds very simple, and it is, but it's also quite fun to get the achievements associated with it. Tea makes a frequent appearance in the routes (as this is a formal atmosphere).WritingThe writing in this game, hands down is GORGEOUS. Storytelling at it's finest, ladies and gents. While there are a few flaws (from translation) overall it is very well-written. I didn't notice any sort of plot holes within the writing, and the dialogue for each character was pretty good. Their inner-thoughts and such fit very well with their personalities. The only awkward thing was when the dialogue box switched over to one of the princesses, and it was difficult to tell who was talking until they said ""I, Leira, think..."". I knew Irell was not talking, but when multiple princesses were involved, things got a little confusing. But this is no reason to dis the game, and this is only a small flaw that occurs maybe 3 times in the entire game so I would not worry about it.ProsExcellent character design and personalities.Interesting main character.Depth in general to things.CGs are great.Complex story with a simple outer-shell.Fun mini-game.Good amount of gameplay.ConsRe-used backgrounds.Not a logical ending sometimes (nit-picking).DLC achievements.Finn's route was a little short.Leira's ending was rushed IMO.Final OpinionIf I was to score it, solid 8/10. There were not that many flaws, and the ones that were weren't huge and contributed to any gameplay. I cannot wait until the sequel comes out, and I will absolutely purchase it! Thanks for reading, and consider buying this game if you are into VNs!"
,Recommended,323490,18280831,"Posted: 1 October, 2015",all,∮Ñ ๑ î r ∈ ♫,"(此為英文評論,中文讀者請閱覽此文章的第二部分)Oblivious Garden ~Carmina Burana is a chinese visual novel which contains several different endings, making it a dating sim. Unlike other visual novels which are either a complete comedy, or a VN with a total tragic story, this VN contains both kinds endings, the bad and the good endings are completely opposing and are in 2 different extremities.The story involves a man named Irell Reis as the protagonist, he had been fighting for his empire during several years and had always won, but lost an important war. After this, his title of duke was removed and he was expelled for a duration of 3 years before entering this 'oblivious garden'. There are in total 7 princesses, the story goes over 3 of the princesesses and a maid who is working in this garden.With Lin, you will find her second ''spirit'' inside her body and will find their relationship together with the emperor, you will meet the emperor in the end, most moving one for me ^.^.With Dyanna, you will discover her forgotten memories which took place 1000 years ago and will also confront the emperor in the end but for another reason, this route is probably the longest.With Leira, you will know her own history as well as her families, and will still meet the emperor in the end. This route contains a good and a bad ending, with ''almost'' no supernatural content involved.With Finn, the maid, you will find out how she is related to Lin as well as many kinds of difficulties that she was forced to face, the emperor will be waiting for you in the ending just like the 3 previous routes. This route is the shortest.Depending on your choices, these stories can go differently, every route has it's specialities, some of them contains both positive and negative endings,but most of them ends happily,there are also some extra bad endings that will occur if you change the choices of routes for each characters too many times. I won't go further in since you can find more details in the strategy guide.From the perspective of comedies such as nekopara or sakura series, this VN contains less whimsical or funny content, the story of Oblivious Garden is rather serious but more touching and beautiful. If you are to find the funniest route which possesses the most jokes, I will suggest you to try Leira's route, the dialogue between Irell and Leira are not too friendly (no bad words) but sometimes funny ( since Leira is a tsundere x) ). Leira and Lin are my personally favourite characters, I started with Lin's route at first when I began to go through this visual novel.To the graphics I found this game a bit inferior than the other VNs, but it doesn't matter a lot to me, the most important point is the story. I have to admit that the soundtrack of this game is really nice, just lacking a bit of horror musics. There are Opening, Identical Conflict which I've fallen in love with for example. I would rather recommend the music fans among the VN fans to buy it's original soundtrack if you like this game. (I didn't forget about the translation issues, for me, it was fine because I had played entirely in chinese, sorry for not giving an opinion on it).Positive remarks ++nice storyline, very touching+multi-endings+nice soundtracks+characters in huge contrasts in terms of personalities+additional content from dlc white day and memories+graphics of the images in the album are well made+fantasy content making the story even more exciting and more interesting+nice background imagesNegative remarks --graphics not very well made in general-(little issue) lack of horror background soundtracks which can create an atmosphere of fear in some moments遺忘庭園是一本中國式視覺小說, 其中包含著許多各種不同的結局。不同於其他以喜劇,鬧劇或是以悲劇收場的VN,這本小說不僅包含快樂和悲傷結局,比起另一本巨作’’刻痕’’以14種不同的結局所呈現的悲傷場面,遺忘庭園把好的和壞的結局以兩種不同的極端予以呈現。故事裡敘述著一名叫做艾爾‧里斯的男子的生平經歷,從一名連戰皆捷的將軍,由於在一次重要的戰役中被敵方用巫術暗算而慘敗,轉變為一名不僅被剝奪了爵位,而且被放逐了四年的’’叛徒’’。三年後,經過皇帝的傳昭,進入了遺忘庭園並成為了七位公主的劍術導師兼神積劇主演。故事內容包含了其中的三位公主,以及另外一名在遺忘庭園服務的女僕主管。如果玩家選擇了冷湛凝(琳)的故事線,便會在故事中發現琳的第二人格以及他們與皇帝的關係,玩家將會在最後的戰鬥前遇見皇帝。如果玩家選擇了狄安娜的故事線,將會逐漸地找出狄安娜在1000年前所遭遇的慘烈戰役及眾神分裂的前因後果,在最後關頭遇上皇帝並與其決一死戰。個人覺得這條故事線是四條線中最長,也是最令人感動的一條線。如果玩家選擇了萊拉的故事線,就會逐漸發掘出萊拉自己的來歷和其王族所遭遇的一連串事件,在故事結束前也會遇到皇帝。這條線有一個好結局和一個壞結局,是唯一一條幾乎沒有任何與’’魔法’’相關的內容。如果玩家選擇了菲茵的故事線,那就會看到菲茵和琳之間的關係,亦會發現其被皇帝虐待的事實和來龍去脈,和其他故事線一樣,皇帝仍然會在最後關頭出現。此線為所有故事線中最短的。視乎玩家的選擇而定,這些故事會分出多條故事內容,每一條線都有他們的特點和必玩之處,其中有些悲慘的結局,但大部分都是好的。玩家也可以在一直選不同角色線的情況下遇上一,兩個壞結局。就這樣,剩下的請玩家自行發掘,選擇的方法的話,攻略裡都有寫。相較於像nekopara或sakura系列以鬧劇為主題的視覺小說,遺忘庭園比較正經,也比較動人。如果玩家想問出最會讓人笑的故事線的話,個人會回答萊拉線,其故事線不但描寫出了主角艾爾和萊拉在一開始所擁有的不愉快的回憶,同時也包含了許多惡搞人的笑話。個人最喜歡萊拉和琳的個性,也是從琳的故事線開始閱覽這本視覺小說的。個人認為此小說的畫風,比起其他視覺小說品質稍微低下了一點點,不過這並不是大問題,視覺小說的重點是故事的內容而不是其畫風的素質(只要別太差就好)。此視覺小說擁有動聽的背景音樂,個人最喜歡所有背景音樂中兩首:’’開場’’和’’永恆衝突’’。不過,個人認為稍微缺少了點令人聽了毛骨悚然的恐怖音樂算是一處可惜的地方。個人推薦此小說的原聲大碟給所有的VN音樂粉絲,尤其是此遊戲的愛好者。優點 ++動人的故事+多結局+令人賞心悅目的原聲大碟+每個角色都擁有著完全不同的個性+White Day和Memories的額外故事情節+精美的album圖畫+超自然(魔法)內容將故事描寫得更加熱血及引人注目+美麗的背景圖畫缺點 –-遊戲中的人物(對話時的)畫風不是非常好-缺少了點以恐怖為主題的音樂,減少了氣氛所帶來的效果"
