76561198321100261,Not Recommended,323490,28581745,"Posted: 23 December, 2016",all,KindMoonHuntress,"character design is nice...but the backgrounds could use a bit of work. Also,  the way the VN is translated has some major problems,. For example, there are passages where I absoultely have no idea what the main character is trying to say or describing just because of its terrible choice of words. Some grammar confusion, as well as wrong pronouns etc..There are parts where I scratched my head, thinking I might have skipped a crucial scene but it turned out that I skipped nothing and THERE ARE NO SCENES TO FILL ME IN THAT IS IN THE GAME. It assumes the player knows what is going on, which doesn't help at all with the confusing plot of  most of the love interests' routes in the game.That being said, the characters are wonderfully developed. They are fully fleshed out for us to see as people..which is really the most surprising aspect of the game. At first, I thought that I would hate particular characters based on their appearances ( predictable stereotypes and cliche tropes), but thankfully, it was the opposite. After finishing the game, I ended up admiring the main female characters for their wonderful portrayals.Lastly, the routes leave quite a lot to be desired. There are routes that are so similar to each other in plot that there really is no point in expecting anything mindblowing ... Lazy writing at its best.All in all, this game COULD have been wonderful if it had a better translation and some  serious work and thought put into its writing.  Unfortunately, its only saving grace is its characters.DON'T BUY IT UNLESS IT'S REALLY CHEAP AND YOU'RE DESPERATE"
